OL,3,CMiners' strike at 40: The story of a
OL,4,Cpit community through one camera lens
OL,6,F"So the person that I worked with
OL,7,Fthought that perhaps if some
OL,8,Fphotographs came out from these
OL,9,Fplaces, would that challenge the
OL,10,Fperceptions of what was being
OL,11,Fportrayed as the strike?"
OL,13,FKeith said he and the community bonded
OL,14,Fquickly - him becoming "their
OL,15,Fphotographer".
OL,17,F"They looked after me, come thick or
OL,18,Fthin," he continued. "It was just
OL,19,Flovely and relaxed, they didn't look
OL,20,Fto the camera. They just got on with
OL,21,Fit and I photographed as best I could."
