OL,3,CMiners' strike at 40: The story of a
OL,4,Cpit community through one camera lens
OL,6,F"And below that were lined police with
OL,7,Friot helmets on, and that just seemed
OL,8,Fto crystallise all of that chaos in
OL,9,Fthe presence of a really domestic
OL,10,Fenvironment."
OL,12,FFrom soup kitchens and people watching
OL,13,FTV at home, to scenes of violence and
OL,14,Fclashes between miners and police,
OL,15,FKeith's pictures are a permanent
OL,16,Freminder of the strike.
OL,18,FThey are also a source of pride.
