OL,3,CMiners' strike at 40: The story of a
OL,4,Cpit community through one camera lens
OL,6,F"It was actually a huge privilege and
OL,7,FI pinch myself looking back to think
OL,8,Fthat I was here," he said. "I was
OL,9,Faccepted by so many people, I was
OL,10,Fsupported by so many people.
OL,12,F"And also, that what I did resonates
OL,13,Fforty years later - they still move me.
OL,15,F"I still go through those pictures and
OL,16,Fthey move me because I can remember
OL,17,Fexactly the moment when those
OL,18,Fphotographs were happening."
